<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="242" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,1852,2059]" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,487,1852,1878]" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">Distribution and Habitat</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[515,757,1852,1879]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="242" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis box="[515,757,1852,1879]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">Croton bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected so far in the Brazilian State of 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[224,291,1888,1914]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1132,1154]" captionTargetBox="[193,1390,371,1086]" captionTargetId="figure-106@4.[151,1436,353,1108]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Croton bacupariensis, showing the only two localities where the species was collected until now in the Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794883/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), in open vegetation on sandy soils of dunes near the sea level, around lagoons.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,1852,2059]" box="[189,947,1924,1951]" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,313,1924,1950]" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">Phenology</emphasis>
—Flowers and fruts found in January, May and October.
</paragraph>
