<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="243" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1604,2062]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1604,1630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Etymology</emphasis>
—The specific epithet refers to the type-locality, Praia do Bacupari, in the Municipality of Mostardas, 
<collectingRegion box="[136,348,1640,1666]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[359,431,1640,1666]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1604,2062]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,576,1676,1702]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Suggested Conservation Status</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[604,855,1676,1702]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis box="[604,855,1676,1702]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be considered Critically endangered (CR) according to the 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[328,480,1712,1738]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" refId="ref2742" refString="IUCN (2017) Guidelines for using the IUCN red list categories and criteria. Version 13. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee of the IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed March 2021)." type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
criteria B1 b(I,ii,iii,iv,v)C1. Its area of occupation (AOO) is 
<quantity box="[1178,1285,1712,1740]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" unit="km" value="8.0">8.000 km</quantity>
² and only two populations of the species were found on sandy soil in the municipality of Mostardas, around salt lagoons, an area that is rapidly being occupied by real estate development.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="244" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1604,2062]" lastBlockId="4.[136,1452,158,329]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="244" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1820,1846]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Comments</emphasis>
—While 
<taxonomicName box="[427,675,1820,1846]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis box="[427,675,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the sandy soils of the dunes, near lagoons in the municipality of Mostardas, Rio Grande do Sul state, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1864" box="[735,876,1856,1882]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gnaphalii">
<emphasis box="[735,876,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">C. gnaphalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the Pampa’s grasslands, in 
<collectingCountry box="[136,250,1892,1918]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[260,358,1892,1918]" name="Uruguay" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[410,618,1892,1918]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, in Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[763,834,1892,1918]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, growing mostly in rocky soils. 
<taxonomicName box="[1186,1427,1892,1918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis box="[1186,1427,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here classified in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pax" authorityYear="1890" baseAuthorityName="Muller Argoviensis" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[323,619,1928,1954]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Lamprocroton">
<emphasis box="[323,401,1928,1954]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[459,619,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Lamprocroton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the presence of a lepidote indumentum,leaves without petiolar glands, and bifid styles with four terminal tips. The following species occur in the same environment: 
<taxonomicName authority="Croizat (1942: 1)" authorityName="Croizat" authorityPageNumber="1" authorityYear="1942" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lombardianus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1452,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton lombardianus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Croizat, L." box="[136,325,2000,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref2554" refString="Croizat, L. (1942) Las especies sudamericanas del genero Croton, I - II. Comunicaciones Botanicas del Museo de Historia Natural de Montevideo 1: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1942">Croizat (1942:1)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is distinct by having branches predominantly prostrate, serrate leaves and stellate trichomes (vs. ascending branches, entire leaves and stellate-lepidote trichomes in 
<taxonomicName box="[947,1137,2036,2062]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis box="[947,1137,2036,2062]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">C. bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Croizat" authorityYear="1942" box="[1160,1401,2036,2062]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lombardianus">
<emphasis box="[1160,1401,2036,2062]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton lombardianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently recorded to 
<collectingCountry box="[364,432,158,184]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Valduga, E. &amp; Molz, M. &amp; Cordeiro, I. &amp; Iganci, J." box="[472,708,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" pagination="189 - 194" refId="ref3709" refString="Valduga, E., Molz, M., Cordeiro, I. &amp; Iganci, J. (2021) Novelties in Croton (Euphorbiaceae) from southern South America. Phytotaxa 496: 189 - 194. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 496.2.8" type="journal article" year="2021">
Valduga 
<emphasis box="[570,625,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus (1759: 1275)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="1275" authorityYear="1759" box="[718,1197,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis box="[718,938,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">Croton glandulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[944,1197,158,185]" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" pagination="825 - 1384" refId="ref2993" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1759) Systema Naturae ed. 10, 2. Laurentius Salvius, Stockholm, pp. 825 - 1384." type="book chapter" year="1759">Linnaeus (1759: 1275)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the serrate leaves and stipitate glands at the base of the leaf blade, or at the apex of the petiole (vs. entire leaves without glands in 
<taxonomicName box="[244,434,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis box="[244,434,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">C. bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Baillon (1864: 358)" authorityName="Baillon" authorityPageNumber="358" authorityYear="1864" box="[457,906,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="helichrysum">
<emphasis box="[457,679,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">Croton helichrysum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Baillon, H. E." box="[685,906,230,257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" pagination="257 - 377" refId="ref2413" refString="Baillon, H. E. (1864) Species Euphorbiacearum. Euphorbiacees Americaines. Premiere partie: Amerique austro-orientale. Adansonia 4: 257 - 377." type="journal article" year="1864">Baillon (1864: 358)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the spatulate leaves (vs. elliptic leaves in 
<taxonomicName box="[241,430,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis box="[241,430,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">C. bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lamarck (1786: 211)" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityPageNumber="211" authorityYear="1786" box="[493,903,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanatus">
<emphasis box="[493,660,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">Croton lanatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck, J. B. A. P. M. de" box="[667,903,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" pagination="1 - 400" refId="ref2829" refString="Lamarck, J. B. A. P. M. de (1786) Encyclopedie Methodique, Botanique 2 (1). Panckoucke, Paris &amp; Plomteux, Liege, pp. 1 - 400." type="book chapter" year="1786">Lamarck (1786: 211)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
presents sessile glands at the base of the leaf (vs. leaf glands absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[372,562,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis box="[372,562,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">C. bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
